cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SY. 

The paper presents a technique for developing a network of re-used features using a coarse learning method and gradient-descent fine-tuning. This technique is applicable to various domains, including image classification and protein-structure prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also demonstrates a convolutional implementation on image classification, which suggests a possible fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the selection process related to evolutionary algorithms implies a potential fit for cs.SY (Systems and Control).
